{
  "texts": [
    "However, using coarse-grained instructions also results in a larger solution space.",
    "For example, in MGToolBench, there are 3 hotel-related tools that contain a total of 60 APIs.",
    "For a category-level instruction that requires hotel information, interacting with any of the 60 APIs is considered a reasonable solution.",
    "Having only statement or category-level instructions as training data can limit the diversity and usability of the model, as it may only interact with a few common APIs.",
    "Therefore, we will use all 5 levels of instructions jointly to build our dataset."
  ]
}